cadEquipmentMib.name: cadEquipmentMib

revisions.description: Add cerCamFaultNotification.
Add cerLicenseTypeStr to the noLicenseNotification trap.
Modify list of allowed FPGA faults.
Change upper limit of cerCardDataAllowedPorts and cerCardDataLicensePorts from 1000 to 5000 and updated the range to all values between 0 and 5000.
Change cerCardDataRamSize units from bytes to megabytes.
Add cerSpareModeExtTable
Change upper limit of cerCardDataAllowedPorts and cerCardDataLicensePorts from 256 to 1000.
Remove CerCardSubType dcamOfdmAnnexB
rename dchannelVod to dchannelVideo in PortType
Support 384 downstream channels per DCAM-B
PortType change: remove dchannelSdv(13) and dchannelBroadcast(14)
Add new video channel types.
Add new SFP types.
Change units of Pem sensors to decivolts and deciamps
Change OID of cardTempOutOfRangeNotification to equipmentTraps.19
Remove patch control support.
Add cerCardDataPicModelName, cerCardDataPicMfgRevision, cerCardDataPicMfg, and cerCardDataPicMfgDateTime.
Modify no license notification to include additional information.
Set valid defaults for cerCardDataEntry.
Change syntax of cerCardDataMfgDateTime to DateAndTime.
Add additional patch control support.
Add initial patch support.
Add cerFanAmbientTemperature.
Remove cerPortMacIfIndex and change cerPortDocsIfIndex to ifIndex for noLicenseNotification.
Add noLicenseNotification.
Change cerCardTemperature, cerCardTemperatureHighWarn, cerCardTemperatureHighError from Celsius to value from 1 to 10
Add cerCardDataAllowedPorts.
Add cerCardDataFeedAPresent and cerCardDataFeedBPresent.
Add cerPemStatusEntry
Replace cerCardId with errEvCardId as the index in fpgaErrorEventEntry.
Move RSM admin ports.
Remove cardEntry, portEntry and diskVolumeEntry
Add more support for fans.
Add support for committed software versions.
Add initial fan support.
Add trap inhibit for card overload.
Incorporate new chassis structure.
Move card version information into a separate table.
Initial changes for E6.
Change syntax of cmIpAddress from IpAddress to OCTET STRING to handle IPv4 and v6.
Add restrictions on the size of some strings in card table.
Add shelf id back into trap messages.
Add ranges for allowable card temperatures.
Remove portGroupId since cable-mac replaced this MIB object. Add shelfNumber to portPrStateChange, portSecStateChange and portDplxStatusChange to match the variable binding list seen on trap monitor.
Additional support for disk sizes.
Initial support for MPM carrier cards.
Support various levels of temperature warnings.
Allowed Event Ids to range 0x00000000 to 0xFFFFFFFF for fpgaErrorEvent Table.
Add port flow control parameters and remove gbic support.
Remove cardSwBuildTime
Remove portMacPortId
Change syntax of portMacPortId from MacPortId to MacPortIdWithInvalid (65536 is invalid)
Add portMacPortId
Add additional variable-binding cmIpAddress cmRegistrationNotification
Add support for RCM module.
Add support for CM registration notification
Add downstream power loss notification.
Add last card reset reason to card table.
Add downstream power visibility to port table.
(1) Add 2 additional variable-bindings to cmResetClearNotification. (2) Add 1 additional variable-binding to cmResetNotification.
Add preliminary support for customized FPGA error event handling.
Add cardSubType, portGroupId and portDocsIfIndex to C4 Port Primary and Secondary Trap.
(1) Modify the TEXTUAL-CONVENTION of TestId. (2) Add diagTestId for cardTestResultNotification.
Added portDescription.
(1) Add support for card temperature trap control. (2) Fix smidump error by changing diskVolumeFileName object mibtree
Add CmResetClear notification.
Add support for logical uchannel port type and preliminary support for extended gbic information.
Add preliminary pic support.
Add card detail support.
Replacing portGroupId with portCardSubType and renaming portDPortId to portGroupId.
Add card temperature monitoring.
Adding portDPortId and portConnectorId objects to portTable to support 2D12U CAM.
Revise audit entries. Add auditAutoScheduling and auditLogOutput control. Remove auditResultNotification
Add support for diskVolume
Undo previous change.
Make cardsubtype backward compatible.
Add support for cardFpgaToCpuSendRate.
Add support for cardSwBuildTime.
Add support for cardUpTime.
Add support for card detected trap.
Add support for card sparing.

cadEquipmentMib.description: This MIB is intended to describe all objects which are used to control and report on the state of an Arris E6 CMTS. These objects are used to perform the following functions on an Arris E6 CMTS: a) provision the cards, ports, and the CMTS itself b) run dianostic tests c) configure auditing parameters d) receive equipment-related traps

TestId.name: TestId
TestId.description: Used as index to Test Tables.

TestType.name: TestType
TestType.description: Indicates whether this is a 'Test', a 'Diagnostic', or unknown.

TestCommand.name: TestCommand
TestCommand.description: A set of commands applicable to this test. A value of noop will do nothing.

TestScheduleCommand.name: TestScheduleCommand
TestScheduleCommand.description: A set of periodic schedule command applicable to this test. This is used in conjunction with the TestSchedule and TestTime to specify the start time of the test. If the TestSchedule value is 0, then the test will be executed once at the time specified by the TestTime. For any other TestSchedule value, the test will be executed at time specified by the TestTime and repeated periodically base on the value specified by TestSchedule. A value of noop will do nothing.

TestSchedule.name: TestSchedule
TestSchedule.description: A set of scheduling interval option applicable to this test only if Schedule is selected. This is recommended for hardware routine exercise (REX). The value expresses in multiple of hours. For example: 1 hour interval, 24 hour interval, 48 hour interval. A value of 0 indicate no scheduling option for this test.

TestTransactionId.name: TestTransactionId
TestTransactionId.description: Transaction Id associated with a test or diagnostic. The EMS must populate the value of this object to be able to correlate the test sent and the result coming back.

CerCamFaultTrapType.name: CerCamFaultTrapType
CerCamFaultTrapType.description: The types of CAM faults that will be logged and a trap sent.

systemClock.name: systemClock
systemClock.description: CMTS local date and time displayed as yyyy-mm-dd,hh:mm:ss.d,+/-hh:mm, where the date is yyyy-mmmm-dd and time in deci-seconds is hh:mm:ss.d, adn teh current offset from GMT is +/-hh:mm. This object is adjusted by teh TZ and DST rules. E.g. 2002-5-26,13;30:15.0,-4:0

trapCounter.name: trapCounter
trapCounter.description: This is the trap sequence number that increments each time a trap is sent. It is persistent across resets.

trapSeverity.name: trapSeverity
trapSeverity.description: Severity level of a Cadant trap.

systemKey.name: systemKey
systemKey.description: The systemKey is a unique string used for Candant's CMTS identification. The EMS uses this key string as well as the sysOid in the MIB-II system group MIB to identify Candant's CMTS's.

cardNumber.name: cardNumber
cardNumber.description: Card Id used in traps. A value 99 indicates an invalid cardNumber.

portNumber.name: portNumber
portNumber.description: Port Id used in traps. A value of 99 indicates an invalid portNumber.

diskDriveNumber.name: diskDriveNumber
diskDriveNumber.description: Disk drive ID use in a Cadant trap. A value of 99 indicates an invalid diskDriveNumber

diskVolumeNumber.name: diskVolumeNumber
diskVolumeNumber.description: Disk volume ID use in a Cadant trap. A value of 99 indicates an invalid diskVolumeNumber

cerCardNumber.name: cerCardNumber
cerCardNumber.description: Card Id used in traps. A value 0 indicates an invalid cardNumber.

cerPortNumber.name: cerPortNumber
cerPortNumber.description: Port Id used in traps. A value of 0 indicates an invalid portNumber.

cerDiskDriveNumber.name: cerDiskDriveNumber
cerDiskDriveNumber.description: Disk drive ID use in a Cadant trap. A value of 0 indicates an invalid diskDriveNumber

cerDiskVolumeNumber.name: cerDiskVolumeNumber
cerDiskVolumeNumber.description: Disk volume ID use in a Cadant trap. A value of 0 indicates an invalid diskVolumeNumber

shelfName.name: shelfName
shelfName.description: A string that represents the name of this machine and may uniquely identify it from other network devices.

cardLastChangeTime.name: cardLastChangeTime
cardLastChangeTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time any of the objects in cardTable last changed.

portLastChangeTime.name: portLastChangeTime
portLastChangeTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time any of the objects in portTable last changed.

cerCardTable.name: cerCardTable
cerCardTable.description: A table of card or circuit pack information.

cerCardEntry.name: cerCardEntry
cerCardEntry.description: A conceptual row containing pertinent information about a card or a circuit pack.

cerCardId.name: cerCardId
cerCardId.description: The unique id of this card within the shelf. The convention of cardId is as follows: - Indices from 1 to 50 [1 - 50] are reserved for Circuit Packs. In this case, the cardId is 1 plus the 0-based slot number. - Indices from 51 to 98 [51 - 98] are reserved for Auxilliary Devices in within a shelf. Auxilliary Devices or Modules could be Fan Module, Power Module. In this case, the cerCardName and cerCardType indentify the Auxilliary Devices. Not all of row attributes are applicable for Auxilliary Devices.

cerCardName.name: cerCardName
cerCardName.description: This is the name of the card, if it has one.

cerCardType.name: cerCardType
cerCardType.description: The type of card, if any. For example Ecard, Fcard, Dcard or Ucard If the slot is empty, the value would be 'empty'.

cerCardSubType.name: cerCardSubType
cerCardSubType.description: The cardType alone may not be specific enough to fully describe the type of card that is in this slot. For example, a card type of Dcard might have a more specific type of 1D8U with integrated upconverter. If the card needs no further specificication that the cardType, then the value of cardSubType is 'none'. Not yet implemented.

cerCardAdminState.name: cerCardAdminState
cerCardAdminState.description: This is the administrative state of this card.

cerCardPrState.name: cerCardPrState
cerCardPrState.description: This is the primary state of this card.

cerCardSecState.name: cerCardSecState
cerCardSecState.description: This is the secondary state of this card.

cerCardDplxStatus.name: cerCardDplxStatus
cerCardDplxStatus.description: This is the duplexing status of this card.

cerCardAction.name: cerCardAction
cerCardAction.description: Write-only action performed on this card.

cerCardTrapInh.name: cerCardTrapInh
cerCardTrapInh.description: If a bit is set, the corresponding state change trap will not be sent.

cerCardNumPorts.name: cerCardNumPorts
cerCardNumPorts.description: Number of ports this card contains.

cerCardDetected.name: cerCardDetected
cerCardDetected.description: CardType dectected automatically by the CMTS.

cerCardSubDetected.name: cerCardSubDetected
cerCardSubDetected.description: CardSubType dectected automatically by the CMTS.

cerCardFwUpdateStatus.name: cerCardFwUpdateStatus
cerCardFwUpdateStatus.description: Set to TRUE if a firmware update is in progress or has been done, else set to FALSE.

cerCardSpareGroupId.name: cerCardSpareGroupId
cerCardSpareGroupId.description: The cardId of the spare group leader for this sparing group. This value will be set to the invalid card id for all cards not associated with a sparing group.

cerCardSpareGroupMode.name: cerCardSpareGroupMode
cerCardSpareGroupMode.description: The admin mode of the spare group leader for this sparing group. This value will be set to the invalid card id for all cards not associated with a sparing group.

cerCardUpTime.name: cerCardUpTime
cerCardUpTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the primary state for this card made a transition from OOS to IS.

cerCardTemperature.name: cerCardTemperature
cerCardTemperature.description: The current relative temperature of the card. (1=coolest, 10=hottest)

cerCardPicDetected.name: cerCardPicDetected
cerCardPicDetected.description: The type of PIC detected in this slot.

cerCardLastResetReason.name: cerCardLastResetReason
cerCardLastResetReason.description: The reason for the latest card recovery.

cerCardTemperatureHighWarn.name: cerCardTemperatureHighWarn
cerCardTemperatureHighWarn.description: The relative temperature of the card at which warnings are generated.

cerCardTemperatureHighError.name: cerCardTemperatureHighError
cerCardTemperatureHighError.description: The relative temperature of the card at which recoveries are initiated.

cerCardAnnex.name: cerCardAnnex
cerCardAnnex.description: The annex of the downstream channels associated with the card.

cerCardNumRfConnectors.name: cerCardNumRfConnectors
cerCardNumRfConnectors.description: Number of RF ports this card contains.

cerCardDataTable.name: cerCardDataTable
cerCardDataTable.description: This table shows the contains version information for the modules installed.

cerCardDataEntry.name: cerCardDataEntry
cerCardDataEntry.description: A conceptual row containing pertinent information about a card or a circuit pack.

cerCardDataSerialNum.name: cerCardDataSerialNum
cerCardDataSerialNum.description: This is the serial number of the card.

cerCardDataFwVersion.name: cerCardDataFwVersion
cerCardDataFwVersion.description: This is the firmware or FPGA version number of the card.

cerCardDataHwVersion.name: cerCardDataHwVersion
cerCardDataHwVersion.description: This is the hardware version of the card.

cerCardDataHwDeviations.name: cerCardDataHwDeviations
cerCardDataHwDeviations.description: This is the set of hardware deviations for the card.

cerCardDataSwVersion.name: cerCardDataSwVersion
cerCardDataSwVersion.description: This is the software version of the card.

cerCardDataCpuType.name: cerCardDataCpuType
cerCardDataCpuType.description: The current CPU type of the card.

cerCardDataCpuSpeed.name: cerCardDataCpuSpeed
cerCardDataCpuSpeed.description: The current CPU speed of the card.

cerCardDataBusSpeed.name: cerCardDataBusSpeed
cerCardDataBusSpeed.description: The current bus speed of the card.

cerCardDataRamSize.name: cerCardDataRamSize
cerCardDataRamSize.description: The current size of installed RAM of the card.

cerCardDataNorFlashSize.name: cerCardDataNorFlashSize
cerCardDataNorFlashSize.description: The current size of installed FLASH of the card.

cerCardDataNandFlashSize.name: cerCardDataNandFlashSize
cerCardDataNandFlashSize.description: The current size of installed FLASH of the card.

cerCardDataFpgaSource.name: cerCardDataFpgaSource
cerCardDataFpgaSource.description: The source of the running version of the FPGAs on the card.

cerCardDataBootVersion.name: cerCardDataBootVersion
cerCardDataBootVersion.description: The current versions of the boot loaders installed on the card.

cerCardDataLastBootVersion.name: cerCardDataLastBootVersion
cerCardDataLastBootVersion.description: The last version of the boot loader used on the card.

cerCardDataLastBootSource.name: cerCardDataLastBootSource
cerCardDataLastBootSource.description: The source of the version of the bootloader last used on the card.

cerCardDataPicSerialNum.name: cerCardDataPicSerialNum
cerCardDataPicSerialNum.description: This is the serial number of the PIC.

cerCardDataPicHwVersion.name: cerCardDataPicHwVersion
cerCardDataPicHwVersion.description: This is the hardware version of the PIC.

cerCardDataPicHwDeviations.name: cerCardDataPicHwDeviations
cerCardDataPicHwDeviations.description: This is the set of hardware deviations for the PIC.

cerCardDataPicModelNum.name: cerCardDataPicModelNum
cerCardDataPicModelNum.description: This is the model number of the PIC.

cerCardDataPartModelNum.name: cerCardDataPartModelNum
cerCardDataPartModelNum.description: Name of the model of this product (FRU).

cerCardDataProductVersion.name: cerCardDataProductVersion
cerCardDataProductVersion.description: Version of the model of this product (FRU).

cerCardDataCommittedSwVersion.name: cerCardDataCommittedSwVersion
cerCardDataCommittedSwVersion.description: This is the software version of the card.

cerCardDataFeedAPresent.name: cerCardDataFeedAPresent
cerCardDataFeedAPresent.description: This object indicates whether power feed A is present or not.

cerCardDataFeedBPresent.name: cerCardDataFeedBPresent
cerCardDataFeedBPresent.description: This object indicates whether power feed B is present or not.

cerCardDataAllowedPorts.name: cerCardDataAllowedPorts
cerCardDataAllowedPorts.description: This object indicates the allowed number of licensed ports.

cerCardDataLicenseAnnex.name: cerCardDataLicenseAnnex
cerCardDataLicenseAnnex.description: This object shows the annex associated with the license.

cerCardDataLicensePorts.name: cerCardDataLicensePorts
cerCardDataLicensePorts.description: This object indicates the number of ports associated with the license.

cerCardDataLicenseDate.name: cerCardDataLicenseDate
cerCardDataLicenseDate.description: This object indicates the date associated with the license.

cerCardDataPatchVersions.name: cerCardDataPatchVersions
cerCardDataPatchVersions.description: This is the patch version(s) running on the card.

cerCardDataPicModelName.name: cerCardDataPicModelName
cerCardDataPicModelName.description: This is the model name of the PIC.

cerCardDataPicMfgRevision.name: cerCardDataPicMfgRevision
cerCardDataPicMfgRevision.description: This is the manufacture revision of the PIC.

cerCardDataPicMfg.name: cerCardDataPicMfg
cerCardDataPicMfg.description: This is the manufacturer of the PIC.

cerCardDataPicMfgDateTime.name: cerCardDataPicMfgDateTime
cerCardDataPicMfgDateTime.description: This object indicates the date associated with the PIC.

cerPortEntry.name: cerPortEntry
cerPortEntry.description: A conceptual row containing pertinent information about a cerPort owned by a card.

cerPortCardId.name: cerPortCardId
cerPortCardId.description: The unique id of the card this cerPort belongs to.

cerPortId.name: cerPortId
cerPortId.description: The unique id of this cerPort within a card. the the cardId and cerPortId uniquely identify a port

cerPortAdminState.name: cerPortAdminState
cerPortAdminState.description: The Admin state of this cerPort

cerPortPrState.name: cerPortPrState
cerPortPrState.description: The primary state of this cerPort

cerPortSecState.name: cerPortSecState
cerPortSecState.description: The secondary state of this cerPort

cerPortAction.name: cerPortAction
cerPortAction.description: Write-only action performed on a Port.

cerPortTrapInh.name: cerPortTrapInh
cerPortTrapInh.description: If a bit is set, the corresponding state change trap will not be sent.

cerPortNumChans.name: cerPortNumChans
cerPortNumChans.description: Number of channels this cerPort contains.

cerPortDocsIfIndex.name: cerPortDocsIfIndex
cerPortDocsIfIndex.description: This object indicates the location of an interface in the cerPort table that represents this port. A value of 0 indicates that this cerPort does not have an association in the Iftable.

cerPortMacAddress.name: cerPortMacAddress
cerPortMacAddress.description: The physical address value for this card. This value is used to populate the ifPhysAddress field in the IfTable and other Tables in docsis RFC MIBs.

cerPortMode.name: cerPortMode
cerPortMode.description: The desired operating mode of an ethernet cerPort. Not yet implemented.

cerPortDetectedMode.name: cerPortDetectedMode
cerPortDetectedMode.description: The current operating mode of an ethernet cerPort.

cerPortBgpId.name: cerPortBgpId
cerPortBgpId.description: The bridge group cerPort id for this port.

cerPortConnectorId.name: cerPortConnectorId
cerPortConnectorId.description: For a DOCSIS or EQAM type port, this is the rear PIC connector. Otherwise, the value of this object is invalid.

cerPortCardSubType.name: cerPortCardSubType
cerPortCardSubType.description: The CardSubType of the card this cerPort belongs to.

cerPortDescription.name: cerPortDescription
cerPortDescription.description: A persistent copy of ifAlias for this interface.

cerPortCurrDsPower.name: cerPortCurrDsPower
cerPortCurrDsPower.description: The latest downstream power level reported by the port. This is valid on for ports of type dport.

cerPortMinDsPower.name: cerPortMinDsPower
cerPortMinDsPower.description: The latest downstream power level recerPorted by the port. This is valid only for downstream ports.

cerPortMaxDsPower.name: cerPortMaxDsPower
cerPortMaxDsPower.description: The latest downstream power level recerPorted by the port. This is valid only for downstream ports.

cerPortTxFlowControlMode.name: cerPortTxFlowControlMode
cerPortTxFlowControlMode.description: The transmit flow control settings for this port (network ports only).

cerPortRxFlowControlMode.name: cerPortRxFlowControlMode
cerPortRxFlowControlMode.description: The receive flow control settings for this port (network ports only).

cerPortTxFlowControlDetected.name: cerPortTxFlowControlDetected
cerPortTxFlowControlDetected.description: The recerPorted transmit flow control settings for this port (network ports only).

cerPortRxFlowControlDetected.name: cerPortRxFlowControlDetected
cerPortRxFlowControlDetected.description: The recerPorted receive flow control settings for this port (network ports only).

cerPortMacIfIndex.name: cerPortMacIfIndex
cerPortMacIfIndex.description: The MAC IfIndex currently associcated with the upstream or downstream port.

cerPortGroupId.name: cerPortGroupId
cerPortGroupId.description: The unique id of port group associated with this port.

cerPortGroupPortId.name: cerPortGroupPortId
cerPortGroupPortId.description: The unique id of this port in the port group.

cerDiskVolumeTable.name: cerDiskVolumeTable
cerDiskVolumeTable.description: A table of disk volume information.

cerDiskVolumeEntry.name: cerDiskVolumeEntry
cerDiskVolumeEntry.description: A conceptual row containing pertinent information about a disk volume

cerDiskVolumeCardId.name: cerDiskVolumeCardId
cerDiskVolumeCardId.description: The unique id of the card this disk volume belongs to.

cerDiskVolumeDriveId.name: cerDiskVolumeDriveId
cerDiskVolumeDriveId.description: The unique id of the disk drive this disk volume belongs to. A value of 99 indicates an invalid disk drive

cerDiskVolumeId.name: cerDiskVolumeId
cerDiskVolumeId.description: The unique id of this disk volume. the cerDiskVolumeCardId, the diskVolumeDiskId, and the. A value of 99 indicate an invalid volume

cerDiskVolumeName.name: cerDiskVolumeName
cerDiskVolumeName.description: The name of the disk volume.

cerDiskVolumeSize.name: cerDiskVolumeSize
cerDiskVolumeSize.description: The disk volume size in units of 2048 bytes.

cerDiskVolumeUsageCriticalThreshold.name: cerDiskVolumeUsageCriticalThreshold
cerDiskVolumeUsageCriticalThreshold.description: Usage percentage level when exceed will cause a cerDiskVolumeUsageNotification trap to be sent with cerDiskVolumeUsageLevel of diskVolumeUsageCritical.

cerDiskVolumeUsageMajorThreshold.name: cerDiskVolumeUsageMajorThreshold
cerDiskVolumeUsageMajorThreshold.description: Usage percentage level when exceed will cause a cerDiskVolumeUsageNotification trap to be sent with cerDiskVolumeUsageLevel of diskVolumeUsageMajor.

cerDiskVolumeUsageMinorThreshold.name: cerDiskVolumeUsageMinorThreshold
cerDiskVolumeUsageMinorThreshold.description: Usage percentage level when exceed will cause a cerDiskVolumeUsageNotification trap to be sent with cerDiskVolumeUsageLevel of diskVolumeUsageMinor.

cerDiskVolumeAutoDeleteUnusedFile.name: cerDiskVolumeAutoDeleteUnusedFile
cerDiskVolumeAutoDeleteUnusedFile.description: When set to TRUE to the system will automatically delete unused files when cerDiskVolumeUsage exceed the cerDiskVolumeUsageCriticalThreshold value.

cerDiskVolumeTrapInh.name: cerDiskVolumeTrapInh
cerDiskVolumeTrapInh.description: If a bit is set, the corresponding trap will not be sent.

cerDiskVolumeDiskSize.name: cerDiskVolumeDiskSize
cerDiskVolumeDiskSize.description: Total physical disk capacity in bytes.

cerDiskVolumeFileName.name: cerDiskVolumeFileName
cerDiskVolumeFileName.description: The name of a file on the disk volume use for trap notification.

cerFanStatusTable.name: cerFanStatusTable
cerFanStatusTable.description: Status information for the E6 fans.

cerFanStatusEntry.name: cerFanStatusEntry
cerFanStatusEntry.description: A conceptual row containing information about one of the fans.

cerFan1Speed.name: cerFan1Speed
cerFan1Speed.description: The last measured speed of fan1.

cerFan2Speed.name: cerFan2Speed
cerFan2Speed.description: The last measured speed of fan2.

cerFan3Speed.name: cerFan3Speed
cerFan3Speed.description: The last measured speed of fan3.

cerFanLevel.name: cerFanLevel
cerFanLevel.description: The last measured speed level of fans.

cerFanAmbientTemperature.name: cerFanAmbientTemperature
cerFanAmbientTemperature.description: The last measured ambient temperature of fans.

cerPemStatusTable.name: cerPemStatusTable
cerPemStatusTable.description: PEM Status information for the E6 power modules.

cerPemStatusEntry.name: cerPemStatusEntry
cerPemStatusEntry.description: A conceptual row containing information about one of the power modules.

remainInDiagMode.name: remainInDiagMode
remainInDiagMode.description: When set to TRUE, the device being diagnosed will remain in diagnostic state when the diagnostic test is completed. When set to FALSE, the device will revert to its original state when the diagnostic test is completed.

consoleOutput.name: consoleOutput
consoleOutput.description: If true then the diagnostic result will be displayed on the system console.

verboseLevel.name: verboseLevel
verboseLevel.description: Verbose output level for diagnostic console output display. Higher number indicate more detailed output.

diagTestId.name: diagTestId
diagTestId.description: Test Identification Number. Used in cardTestResultNotification variable-binding

cardTestTable.name: cardTestTable
cardTestTable.description: A table of test available for a card.

cardTestEntry.name: cardTestEntry
cardTestEntry.description: A conceptual row containing information about tests or dignostics available for a card.

cardTestIndex.name: cardTestIndex
cardTestIndex.description: Card Identification Number taken from the CardTable. Used as index.

cardTestId.name: cardTestId
cardTestId.description: Test Identification Number. Used as index to test table

cardTestName.name: cardTestName
cardTestName.description: A unique name for this test.

cardTestDescription.name: cardTestDescription
cardTestDescription.description: A short description of the test.

cardTestCommand.name: cardTestCommand
cardTestCommand.description: Command to be execute this test on this shelf

cardTestScheduleCommand.name: cardTestScheduleCommand
cardTestScheduleCommand.description: Schedule Command to be execute this test on this shelf

cardTestResultDesc.name: cardTestResultDesc
cardTestResultDesc.description: Additional information of the test result.

auditAutoScheduling.name: auditAutoScheduling
auditAutoScheduling.description: Enable or disable automatic audit execution.

auditLogOutput.name: auditLogOutput
auditLogOutput.description: Enable or disable logging of error entries to system log.

auditLogThrottle.name: auditLogThrottle
auditLogThrottle.description: Enable or disable audit log output throttling to prevent audit errors from flooding the log.

auditTable.name: auditTable
auditTable.description: A table of test available for a card.

auditEntry.name: auditEntry
auditEntry.description: A conceptual row contains information about Audits.

auditCardId.name: auditCardId
auditCardId.description: Card Identification Number taken from the CardTable. Used as index.

auditId.name: auditId
auditId.description: Unique ID of the internal Audit

auditCommand.name: auditCommand
auditCommand.description: Audit Commands. The runnow command will stop the currently running audit sequence and start executing requested audit immediated. If enabled, automatic audit schedule will be restarted.

auditPassedCount.name: auditPassedCount
auditPassedCount.description: Number of passed entry during previous audit run.

auditFailedCount.name: auditFailedCount
auditFailedCount.description: Number of failed entry during previous audit run.

auditTotalPassedCount.name: auditTotalPassedCount
auditTotalPassedCount.description: Number of cumulative passed entry of all audit runs.

auditTotalFailedCount.name: auditTotalFailedCount
auditTotalFailedCount.description: Number of cumulative failed entry of all audit runs.

cmMacAddress.name: cmMacAddress
cmMacAddress.description: The MAC address for the cable modem

cmVendor.name: cmVendor
cmVendor.description: The vendor name of the cable modem

cmResetReason.name: cmResetReason
cmResetReason.description: The reason for the cable modem to reset

cmUChannelID.name: cmUChannelID
cmUChannelID.description: The CMTS upstream channel ID which is connected to the cable modem

cmPrimarySID.name: cmPrimarySID
cmPrimarySID.description: The primary Service Identifier (SID) assigned by the CMTS associated with the cable modem

cmResetStatus.name: cmResetStatus
cmResetStatus.description: The cable modem status before it resets

cmResetUpTime.name: cmResetUpTime
cmResetUpTime.description: This value indicates how long in hundreds of seconds the cable modem is up since it is initial ranged

cmResetInfo.name: cmResetInfo
cmResetInfo.description: The additional information for the cable modem to reset

cmIpAddress.name: cmIpAddress
cmIpAddress.description: The IP Address of the cable modem

fpgaErrorEventTable.name: fpgaErrorEventTable
fpgaErrorEventTable.description: Overrides default handling of FPGA error events.

fpgaErrorEventEntry.name: fpgaErrorEventEntry
fpgaErrorEventEntry.description: A conceptual row containing information about FPGA error event handling.

errEventId.name: errEventId
